cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the specification and verification of properties in multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of temporal logic and the focus on reasoning about strategies suggest that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category. The involvement of multiple agents and the use of strategies also suggest that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are relevant categories. The complexity analysis and the use of models suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also possible categories.
